  "reconciliation": "The authoritative latencies are separate uninstrumented 20-prefill/500-trace measurements. Profiler signposts are one instrumented iteration; they include trace call, queue, and synchronization overhead. tt-perf-report merges four devices, and summed device rows are not a wall clock because asynchronous device intervals overlap, which is why the long prefill row sum can exceed signpost wall. Short-profile kernel/gap totals and long signposts are therefore accounting views of the same final default, not evidence of an untraced fallback."
